An Act relative to the environmental protection of Joint Base Cape Cod.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 1 of chapter 47 of the acts of 2002, as most recently amended by
2 section 11 of chapter 48 of the acts of 2014, is hereby further amended by striking out the
3 definitions of “Environmental performance standards” and “Joint Base Cape Cod” and inserting
4 in place the following 2 definitions:-
5 "Environmental performance standards", the environmental performance standards
6 included in the final environmental impact report, and any amendments thereto, regarding the
7 activities on the northern 15,000 acres of the Joint Base Cape Cod promulgated under sections 61
8 to 62H, inclusive, of chapter 30 of the General Laws and certified by the secretary of
9 environmental affairs on July 16, 2001.
